The paper deals with the problem of data privacy protection, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), cryptography and security (cs.CR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on constructing privacy channels, which involves evaluating the capacities of channels, a concept that is central to information theory. Therefore, cs.IT is the most likely sub-category. However, since the paper also deals with privacy and security, cs.CR is also a likely sub-category. The paper also involves constructing privacy-preserving mechanisms for querying datasets, which involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper uses results from information theory to construct privacy channels, which is a topic that falls under machine learning (cs.LG).
